81.0	Sinclair_Lewis	Sinclair Lewis	Harry Sinclair Lewis (February 7, 1885 â€“ January 10, 1951) was an American novelist, short-story writer, and playwright. In 1930, he became the first writer from the United States to be awarded the Nobel Prize in Literature, "for his vigorous and graphic art of description and his ability to create, with wit and humor, new types of characters." His works are known for their insightful and critical views of American society and capitalist values, as well as for their strong characterizations of modern working women.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/0a/Sinclair_Lewis_1930.jpg
